, "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}, {"id": 889209675, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw4ODkyMDk2NzU=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-iterators", "name": "A-iterators", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Iterators"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 8, "created_at": "2020-08-11T16:45:47Z", "updated_at": "2020-10-20T20:37:35Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hi guys,\r\n\r\nI want to make a small requirement for *Iteration* to support foldmap.\r\n\r\n**foldmap** provides an accumulator for mapping like this:\r\n\r\n[v0, v1, v2, v3] \r\n\r\n  ->  [v0, v0+v1, v0+v1+v2, v0+v1+v2+v3]\r\n\r\n  ->  [v0, v0*(v0+v1), v0*(v0+v1)*(v0+v1+v2), v0*(v0+v1)*(v0+v1+v2+v3)]\r\n\r\nIn this way, **foldmap** can be composed conveniently than **map**.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn funny(v: Vec<i32>) -> Vec<i32> {\r\n\tv.iter()\r\n\t\t.foldmap(0, |acc, x| acc + x)\r\n                .foldmap(1, |acc, x| acc * x)\r\n\t\t.collect()\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @zhibo501 in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/75367#issuecomment-671466066_", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/75410/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/75410/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}